        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-10-14 15:26:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAs for the other patchset, I don't see the point to split tox lists in multiple runs.\nFor a very small gain in duration (not so sure), you would have quickly to manage excludes per branch.\n\nTox could be the only entry point and then you would only define default env lists per branches.\nHere it asks for backports or to add exclude per stream.\n\nHere is an example excluding streams:\nhttps://git.opnfv.org/releng/tree/jjb/functest/xtesting.yaml#n217",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
